Package ru.nsu.fit.smolyakov.recordbook.internal

Class Mark

java.lang.Object
ru.nsu.fit.smolyakov.recordbook.internal.Mark
public class Mark extends Object
Provides a functionality to operate with marks specified at input JSON.

Implements a Mark constructor which assumes that String parameter contains comma-separated type of attestation ("exam", "differentiated_credit" or "credit") and a value in range of 2 and 5 in first two cases or "pass" or "fail" string literal in a third one, as well as static of(java.lang.String) method to construct an instance.

"pass" is treated as mark valued 5 and "fail" is treated as 2.

    • Mark

      public Mark(String field)
      Constructs an instance of Mark class based on a specified text representation. field is supposed to be a comma-separated type of attestation ("exam", "differentiated_credit" or "credit") and a value in range of 2 and 5 in first two cases or "pass" or "fail" string literal in a third one, otherwise this method throws a IllegalArgumentException.

      Credits are not treated as valueable, just "pass" or "fail".

      Parameters:
      field - a specified text representation of a mark

      IllegalArgumentException - if field has incorrect format
